@chapter GCC & Grep Colors

@float Figure,fig:screenshot_gcc-grep
@center @image{screenshots/bashstyle-ng_gcc-grep,,, BashStyle-NG GCC & Grep Colors, png}
@caption{GCC & Grep Colors}
@end float

@heading GCC Colors

@defvr {Settings} use_gcc_colors Enable GCC Colors
This master switch will make @b{BashStyle-NG} adjust the colors for @code{gcc}.
@end defvr

The following settings allow you to adjust the specific types of text messages
to be colored by @b{BashStyle-NG}'s predefinied colors.

Caret = the @code{^} shown to point to a specific part of the code
Locus = location information (line, column, etc.)

@heading Grep Colors

@defvr {Settings} use_grep_colors
This master switch will make @b{BashStyle-NG} adjust the colors for @code{grep}.
@end defvr

The following settings allow you to adjust the specific types of text messages
to be colored by @b{BashStyle-NG}'s predefinied colors.

selected match = the actual match
context match = lines before or after the selected match displayed to give context
information, enabled via @code{-A}, @code{-B} or @code{-C} flags.
